raw_data.title: Bed Bug Technician
raw_data.description: Will visually inspect to identify any residential, commercial, and industrial locations for bed bug infestation with the help of highly trained canines. Utilizes treatment methods such as steaming, and pesticide application, while protecting the affected environment. Must have thorough knowledge of the hazards and safety precautions associated with bed bug removal. Study preliminary reports and diagrams of infested area and determine treatment type required to eliminate and prevent recurrence of infestation. Manages bed bug infestations through comprehensive treatment strategies that incorporate a variety of techniques and vigilant monitoring.  Additional responsibilities include: Use steamers safely where necessary. Move furniture if needed. Lift at least 40 lbs. Use chemicals according to label. Sit for an extended period of time (driving). Maintain vehicles and keeping chemical inventory updated. Pick up/Drop off working dogs (dog handlers only) Bend, kneel, and climb stairs. Use the proper personal protective equipment according to chemical labels and procedures.

raw_data.title: Commercial/Industrial Technician (Non-Residential)
raw_data.description: Will visually inspect to identify any bed bug or termite infestation in a commercial or industrial space. Identifies pest problem and appropriate solution, applies chemical or trap, and removes pests. Utilizes treatment methods such as steaming, and pesticide application while protecting the affected environment. Manages infestations through comprehensive treatment strategies that incorporate a variety of techniques and vigilant monitoring. Creates barrier to prevents pests from entering any facilities and/or properties. Direct and/or assist other workers in treatment and extermination processes to eliminate and control rodents, insects, and weeds. Manages the applications of pesticides (including organic, natural pesticides and other environmentally sustainable methods), as well as trapping and/or removal of pests.  Additional responsibilities include: Lift at least 40 lbs. Use chemicals according to label. Sit for an extended period of time (driving). Maintain vehicles and keeping chemical inventory updated. Bend, kneel, climb ladders, and climb stairs. Use the proper personal protective equipment according to chemical labels and procedures. Work in all types of weather conditions unless instructed otherwise from management. Example: heavy snow, instructed not to report to work. Have all the necessary equipment on hand for all aspects of commercial work.

raw_data.title: Termite Technician
raw_data.description: Inspects and detects termite infestations and uses a variety of comprehensive extermination strategies to remove termites from residential spaces. Uses chemicals to eliminate termites and modifies structures to eliminate termites and prevent future infestations. May use techniques such as drilling, sweeping, trenching, applying environmentally safe chemicals, and ensuring the removal of all termite colonies with diligent monitoring of the area.  Additional responsibilities include: Lift at least 40 lbs. Use chemicals according to label. Sit for an extended period of time (driving). Maintain vehicles and keeping chemical inventory updated. Bend, kneel, climb ladders, and climb stairs. Use the proper personal protective equipment according to chemical labels and procedures. Work in all types of weather conditions unless instructed otherwise from management. Example: heavy snow, instructed not to report to work. Able to enter and exit crawlspaces. Able to carry and climb a 23 foot ladder. Able to enter and exit attics using pull down stairs/ladder
